## Rules for Color Usage

### ✅ DO
- Use the defined teal gradient for all primary elements
- Use SCSS variables: `$blue`, `$cyan`, `$teal`, `$primary`
- Use CSS custom properties: `var(--bs-app-theme)`, `var(--bs-primary)`
- Apply consistent gradients across similar components
- Use rgba() for hover/focus states with opacity

### ❌ DON'T
- Hardcode hex values in component SCSS
- Use old blue colors (`#1b76ff`, `#6b5ce7`)
- Create custom gradients outside the defined palette
- Use teal for error/danger states (use red)
- Use teal for success states (use green)

## Migration from Blue to Teal
When updating old components:
1. Replace `#1b76ff` → `#108E91` (Deep Teal)
2. Replace `#1bb8ff` → `#33D4C3` (Light Teal)
3. Replace `#6b5ce7` → `#20B6AA` (Mid Teal)
4. Update gradients to teal variants
5. Test contrast ratios for accessibility

## Accessibility
All teal colors meet WCAG AA standards:
- Deep Teal text on white: ✅ 4.5:1
- White text on Deep Teal: ✅ 6.2:1
- Deep Teal on Light Gray: ✅ 5.1:1
